reviews.text: One and Done! I would not return. Ordered 2 small coffees.  No 1/2 and 1/2. "Oh well!" Had I known, I would not have wasted $5.00.  We ordered a bagel w/ cream cheese and lox.  It was very skimpy on the cream cheese, lox, caper, lettuce, tomato and onion.  The bagel was ok.. nothing to rave about.  The breakfast burrito w/ bacon was large, filling and greasy! I was expecting nice crispy bacon...instead it contained soggy, bland turkey bacon or Sizzleen. I guess because it's a kosher bagel shop, I should not have assumed I was getting real bacon.  The description on the menu states bacon or sausage.  It should be clearly stated that it's turkey bacon.  I don't mind paying a premium charge, but not for sub-par food. My order would've been different had I realized they did not have 1/2 and 1/2 or real bacon.  Knowing that upfront, I would probably give them a 3 star rating.. because again.. the bagels are okay but their filling is sub-par.

Really good classic New York bagels. I had the egg and cheese sandwich and although I was skeptical about the suggestion of mozzarella, it was actually very good. The bagel tasted like a real bagel and not just bread.

This place was suggested to us by a friend who claims they get their dough brought in brim NYC? I don’t know for sure if that’s true. But I do know that their bagels are fantastic!! Go early if you want a good selection because they certainly do sell out! My husband loves getting his with lox, whereas I like my everything bagel plain. Just writing about this place makes me hungry. Check it out!
Good bagel here. They made it fast. I order egg and cheese on ET. It's delicious. The restaurant is also nice and clean.

Solid place.  More than bagels.  They have lunch options too.  I had a vegetarian sausage egg and cheese bagel.  Very good.  Half dozen bagels to go were good too.  Very large bagels. Good local stop.

Truly a terrible outlet.  We moved from across town and unfortunately the Dominos in our new neighborhood changed.  The prior one was great - on time, predictable.  This one is ALWAYS later - either they can't find a driver or for some reason the driver decides to take a nap between the store and dropping off our food.  I don't expect much from fast food but there are too many pizza choices to keep selecting this one.

Was one of the worst experience I have ever had. First the place is around three blocks from my house but instead of delivering to me first the driver took my pizza to another town (I live in DC they went to Silver Springs). When I went to the store to complain the Managing Partner told me that if I didn't like it I could leave and then said he was calling the police because I said I was going to write a review on Google.
Tasty pizza and they have good deals sometimes too.

This location specifically, is the worst at “Forgetting” to bring sodas and dipping cups, then won’t refund you. The food I ordered came pretty quickly but was soggy. Please don’t waste your money here.

this location isnt bad its just the effort they make on the pizzas and other foods arent there i usually get burnt food from here ,last time i ordered i got two types of tatter tots  and it did it for me they were both burnt … im disappointed

Today, three adults and three children had chicken and broccoli, singapore noodles and the vegetarian dumplings (steamed). Everyone enjoyed the dishes even a picky toddler who's likings are hard to find. We recommend Mayflower and suggest trying those three dishes.

My family always ordered from here growing up, and I've continued to visit every time I'm in town .  Reliably great food; their stir-fries have wonderfully-seasoned sauces with well-balanced flavors, and the pan-friend dumplings are exceptional.

I’ve been going to Mayflower for about 10 years now and it’s still my favorite Chinese spot. We always gets their general Taos, shrimp & broccoli and shrimp fried rice. Everything is delicious and delivery is pretty quick.
If you want Chinese food, this restaurant must be your best choice, delicious, fresh and timely service, and will continue to buy

The food is quite good! Regrettably, this past year we had two occasion where BOTH times we found pieces of aluminum strands in our food. By sheer luck my family and I have chewed very well our food and we are thankful that the kids haven’t accidentally ingested scraps of metal. (The piece of metal was taken out of the chewed food to show what would’ve been consumed)

Worst Chinese take out I’ve ever had.  Sweet & sour chicken was neither and came without any onion, pepper or pineapple. Cashew chicken was WAY over salted. 2 stars instead of 1 only because vegetable egg foo young was passable, as was beef with snow peas. Delivery was speedy.

Horrible costumer service and delivery. This location has a rude manager and equally rude delivery guy. Food is so so and high prices. The delivery guy is a lazy latino man (both manager and delivery guy have broken english hard to communique with them),he refused to enter the building on 3 different ocaccions just because he is too lazy to come up the elevator. The manager yelled  at me instead of been understanding or apologetic. I will NEVER order anything there again neither my  2 roommates. Don't waste your money at Hunan City.!

Great food! Good clean taste. You can tell the ingredients are fresh and good quality unlike most other simple Chinese places. I have tried multiple items off their menu and I have yet to be let down. You will not be let down

Hunan City is my all-time favorite restaurant for ordering takeout. I get the Plant-based sesame chicken occasionally, sometimes I’ll get the dumplings, other times I’ll get the egg drop soup. It’s all very good. The delivery is reasonably quick, and the delivery guys are all pretty nice. My family also enjoys the crab Rangoon.

This place is the heaven of Chinese food. I ordered the orange chicken with fried rice it was so good I felt like I was in China. Family owned and operated and the owners are so friendly! Alcohol too,  they got endless tall boys for the low.

This is the best Dominican 🇩🇴 food in the area. The mofongo is seasoned well, moist, and tasty. The portion sizes are sharable abd prices are very reasonable. The service is well and the staff are very friendly. Parking is free on Saturday and Sundays.

The place in the inside is ok, but this is the most closest home made food I ever had. Everything is done daily. The parchita juice was a real juice not from frozen concentrate. The mondongo was tastefully. Everything in here was delicious. Certainly this is not my first visit. And the server have a great customer service in here. Highly recommended
Nice hole in the wall-esque type of place. The Mofongo was tasty, but very dry. Everything else we had was delicious, though one could argue it may be a bit in the salty side.

This was my first time having Puerto Rican food and I have to say it was really underwhelming. The carne frita with mofongo was very dry and tasteless. Feels like I was chewing on beef jerky but with no flavor and you’re going to be in for a jaw work out if you order this. The chicken with mofongo was definitely my favorite. The chicken came off of the bones easily and was decently seasoned. I also ordered some fried yucas and they were very dry and hard. For 1.1k reviews with decent rating, I expected the food to be very appetizing and well made but I wasn’t able to finish what I ordered even though I usually have a really big appetite. They were also out of flan and tres leches for dessert. The server was pretty nice but did take a while to come and collect payment when we were done. Honestly I wouldn’t recommend this place if you want to try Puerto Rican food.
Rare gem. This place was amazing! Everything was great, from the ambiance, service,  and taste of the food. Definitely will have to return again.

The portion size are huge so don’t worry about not getting full of rich and kinda healthy food. The only „problem“ I had was the taste but that is something out of my personal point of view. I would like to have more spice but overall good quality.

Great services, wonderful atmosphere, oh the taste food. Very welcoming stop. Suggestion of food was wonderful. Go in and try it. We sat and eat and chat. Full bar of drinks but must try the cinnamon tea.

It was good. Not go out of the way, great, travel from another state amazing. But decent Ethiopian food.

However, a shining highlight was the sauce that gives with the veggie sambusas. Now that was 5 star delicious.

The food is a little Americanized for my tastes... but I get it... and it was still tasty. I like the space though and the staff is good. i did have to wait nearly an hour for my takeout order, but i got there just after a party of 12 ppl ordered... and, the staffing is a bit light on a late Tuesday night (at least until you guys start visiting more! 😜) All in all... i liked it and will be back.

We have had good experiences here when dining in the restaurant, but our takeout order was disappointing. The food was not as described on the menu, items were missing, and our request for mild spice was overlooked. When I called to enquire, the hostess chose to argue with me about what the menu said and how some dishes are spicier than others, even though I always order the same dish. Consistency and better customer service would be advisable.

I love it when I find a great food truck. Just hit the mobile version of Heavenly Wings at 9331 Georgia Ave in Silver Spring on the Exxon parking lot.

Wings were cooked to order in 7 minutes. Came out super crispy and perfectly cooked. Medium level heat was like traditional Buffalo wings.

Server was polite and kind. Definitely worth the stop even if you don’t need gas!

Happened upon this food truck while getting gas and snacks.  Decided to give it a try although my gut feeling and intuition was hesitant.  Should have followed my instincts.  This food was horrible.  Overpriced and disgusting.  The lemon pepper was nonexistent on the lemon pepper wings.  The chicken lacked flavor and did not taste fresh.  Also the other order we had of the spicy wings and fries made my family sick!  Literally a few minutes after eating that horrible chicken they threw up, and everything which confirmed my concerns about it being sanitary and the food fresh. I would never recommend this place and wish I could get my $26 back.  Waste of time and money. I wish I could give it negative stars because I would.

Jeremiah is an absolute treat man. Such a cool kid, his vibes are immaculate and he’s just genuinely kind. Kid has so much going for him in the future. And gotta say, I started off with the hot dogs and he convinced me to try the wings. Ever since, I never went back to the dogs. (Although the DC dogs do be good.) Those lemon pepper just hit differently.

I visited their Germantown station and was completely satisfied from the service to the wings themselves. I ordered hot, lemon pepper,  and old bay flavors. My favorite was the old bay followed by the lemon pepper. The wings were well seasoned, fresh and, crisped...just the way I like them. The French fries almost didn't make it home for dinner 😄. Well done 👏

Anything but heavenly. The wings tasted old. The texture was that of wings that had been sitting and recooked the next day. Barely any sauce on the wings. And the fries were vomit inducing. The tastes like paper. Tasted like they had been recooked several times and were left in an old grease trap. Save your money. This was an atrocious excuse of a meal. I never leave reviews for anything. But this was just insulting.

I’ve been shopping here for a couple of years now. It’s way cheaper than an outside grocery store. The fresh produce is usually hit or miss so I always go the day after a fresh delivery (Wed and Sat I believe). Baggers work for tips, but are painfully slow to the point I’d rather do it myself. (There are some fast guys that I give bigger tips to.) The fresh deli has your basics covered. Reggie is the friendliest guy in the place, love seeing that guy!
Great prices and outstanding customer service. Always a great shopping experience at Forest Glen.
I go weekly sometimes twice a week. Love all the workers and of course the prices can't be beat.
Produce is usually a bit old. Good place to buy pet food.

Good for a small commissary close to DC. Clean store with good parking. Inventory and bakery could be better. Items are easy to find but most are sold out early. Figure out the best day to come or it could be a wasted trip due to low or no inventory.

The smell at the entrance is very good!
On Fridays this place is very busy. Please reserve a table before, I didn't it, so I had to wait around 20min.

Place: Small, clean and nice, even though it was so busy.

Customer service: At the entrance the service could improve. They were polite and did a good job.

Food: They use fresh ingredients, for food, I really liked it. The favorite item was the dessert a Lemon Pie, very good taste.

Price: The price-experience-food to me wasn't the best. I've been in other similar places in the area with best options and prices.

I wasn't planning to eat out tonight but was on my way home when a severe storm induced me to take shelter at Pacci's. I had ordered pasta to go during the pandemic shutdowns and enjoyed it, but I'm not eating bread or pasta right now so I figured I'd have an app or a salad or something.  Enter the specials list, which included salmon with mixed vegetables. Perfect, if I could just be sure they wouldn't overcook it. 😬 I asked for medium rare even though it wasn't a question offered to me. OMG, it was the best thing I've eaten in weeks. The salmon was *perfectly* cooked, and the vegetables were tender and bright-flavored with a hearty infusion of garlic. The mix of veg was great as well - perfectly wilted spinach, 2 kinds of mushrooms, ripe cherry tomatoes, artichoke hearts with just enough texture... and the zucchini.  I had just about convinced myself that I really didn't like zucchini anymore. NEVER MIND, I TAKE IT ALL BACK. The restaurant is surprisingly big, with lots of little cozy nooks perfect for conversation or just catching up on your reading. Service is fantastic from top to bottom.  Add a nice glass of Malbec, and man, next time there's a thunderstorm I might "accidentally" find myself in the neighborhood again...

It's a nice house that has been converted into a restaurant!!

Truly an Italian experience. Pizzas were great. The service was really good and polite. Loved the experience!
Great family brunch option. The food variety was immaculate and I enjoyed the friendly wait staff.
My husband and I love Italian food, this place is small but very cozy, the food is fresh, good portions, pizza mmm mamma mia and the gnocchi you have to try it.

name: The Urban Winery of Silver Spring

reviews.text: We just hosted a party at the Urban Winery for my son and his wife. We invited about 40 people, and had a great space which allowed everyone to mix comfortably, sit, and visit with friends. The food, wine, and service were terrific - we worked closely with Georgia and Damon to put together a set of appetizers that were a big hit. Of course, the wine was great - and they also picked up some beer from one of the nearby microbreweries for our non-wine-loving guests. We enthusiastically recommend the Urban Winery to anyone planning a party.

We loved the aesthetic and the different wine selections. It certainly is an urban location, but very unique for the area (bonus point in our book). The staff was also extremely kind and welcoming. We enjoyed a few flights and the pita/tzatziki appetizer and are looking forward to our next visit.

We stopped at Urban Winery while passing though town and the only negative I can find is that it isn't closer to where we live. The tasting room is in an industrial park and has an elevated brewery vibe. Their wines are delicious, but they also serve local beers, other wines from independent wineries, and even several Greek wines. The owner Damon was friendly, knowledgeable, and super helpful. We will definitely stop in any time we are in the area. I can't wait to try the hop wine (cans!) we got to go. Would definitely recommend to anyone in the area or passing through.

We absolutely loved our experience. The ambience was so warm and inviting. The staff was also very friendly and the different wines in the flights were all so good it was hard to pick a favorite!  I will absolutely be coming back again, SOON.

They have a very nice and relaxing outdoor space. The service was wonderful. They offer a handful of different wine flights. We ordered snacks from their selection making our own version of a charcuterie board.

Saw one of our tires was way low when I left the house. Called the mechanic and he said I could come right over. He immediately pulled the tire, plugged it, and had me on my way in less than 30 minutes from my call. Very pleasant too. Highly recommend.

I came here and was here at 5:20.  The shop said they closed at 5:30.  I explained that I was injured, just wanted my oil changed on my way to my appointment and the manager, Wilfredo, still would not do my oil change.  How long does it really take to change oil?  That’s the type of service I get?  I am not happy at all.
I'm a local, and I have my choice of local garages, but these guys take care of me. They give me what I need, and nothing that I don't, and their prices are the best.

Good place to pop in and out for gas. Is competitively priced for the area, but is better if you use Giant fuel perks or another rewards card. The parking lot is a little hard to get out of with all the traffic on Georgia.

(Note: This station gets no stars from me. Unfortunately, I can't post my review without selecting a star.) I couldn't get my car to start after pumping gas at this Shell station on my way to work this morning. Not only was the mechanic who worked there hesitant to look at my car when I couldn't get it started (I was unable to move my car from the pump so I was blocking other customers), he charged $10 for jump starting it after it was determined that my battery was dead. It took less than a minute and I'm sure that almost anyone else, who's decent and kind, would have done it for free. I wouldn't have been so upset about paying the $10 if it wasn't for both the attendant and mechanic being so rude, unwilling to help, and discourteous. Shame on them.

What’s the point of text updates if they’re just lying? Don’t tell me 10 minutes and then send another text when time’s up saying it’ll be another 15 minutes. Disorganized and slow, plus you have to remind them of your entire order or they will “forget” to give you everything. Dry salad kinda sucks when it’s supposed to come with dressing, but that’s the least of this food truck’s worries. 0/5 for service, 3/5 for taste.

I placed my order and went to pick it up just for this business/food truck to cancel my order 10 minutes after it was supposed to be ready stating the propane was gone and he couldn’t cook my food. He should have stopped taking orders. No certificate for the inconvenience was offered - no, he didn’t care to make this right. Also, the ordering platform does not work on iphone 13, I had to use my laptop and wait only for them to cancel my dinner. I wouldn’t order from there again if someone paid me.

Placed order via Curbside app at 10am for pickup 11:15-11:30am. Received text that food was ready.
Arrived at truck at 11:15 and told a few more minutes. Colleague placed order and received food 5 mins later. I was told they ran out of my order and to order something else. Took another 20 mins as other orders were prepared ahead of mine.
Major problem with communication via the app. The food is good, but the wait is not.

Good food but unauthorized charges. We got a wrap and a sandwich. He quoted us 8 minutes but took over 20 minutes to get us the food. He verbally told us the total as he held out the chip reader and we handed him our card. When we got the Square receipt, it showed that he had added a drink we never requested or received and a tip. (It was just a chip reader device so no offer of tip even came up.) I’m all for supporting a small business in my neighborhood, but adding unauthorized charges is not good practice.

The food was good, but check your receipt!

I hate to give 1 star reviews, but let me tell you why I love writing this one. Note, this involves their food truck.

I ordered a few items online at around 5:15PM and was notified food would be ready by 5:35PM. 5:35 rolls around and I go to the truck. At 5:40PM I spoke to the guy who at that moment told me it would be ten more minutes. I say 'great', and walk away. I come back at 5:50PM. Still not ready, but they say it will be soon. I wait longer, this time out front of the food truck in the freezing cold, not that they control the weather, but I figured they'd be mindful of seeing me and maybe cook my food. Then, I wait with other people until around 6:40PM. At this point I ask about my food again. They say my order is going on right at that moment, so I wait some more. Between 6:40PM and 7:20PM, I stand by and watch multiple other people who had order times well past my estimated order time of 5:35PM, and who ordered significantly more food, receive their orders. At 7:20PM, I ask about my order once more. They say that they're just now starting to cook it, and they'll text me when it's ready. I walk away.

It's now 7:40PM, and I've heard nothing. I don't care that you're busy, but don't lie to me and keep saying my food will be ready soon/is being cooked when it clearly isn't. Especially when you can see I'm standing in the cold waiting for it. It is monumentally disrespectful. I do not believe I will ever be eating with this establishment ever again, strictly based on the horrendous service alone.
Pretty new place, I think it just opened up in mid pandemic.. latin music pumpin' a bit of a bar food with a Dominican twist!! Very nice bar.

My 2nd time coming here, love the music! It’s great place to chill with friends and drink. The food is bomb! Highly recommend the Chicken sushi, chicken wigs and Platno’s . The vibe is nice definitely my go to spot with friends
In this disgusting place it is not safe because they stole my apple phone and my North face jacket, and the owner does not help you at all I will not return to that place, there is no security...

The WORST CLUB EVER !! 1. It’s to small there is no walk way everyone pushing your dropping your drinks. 2. There is only one restroom and it’s disgusting. 3. Owner/ Bartenders we’re sliding people through VIP tables when they had the orange wristband they would let them pass totally unfair . 4. It’s 12:30 and they said 30 mins more till JOE VERAS comes it’s dam 1 am and nothing the club close at 2 so he only singing for 45 minutes? Don’t go here you are wasting your money better off going somewhere else to enjoy . I wasted my money and for Sure not going back .

We Have been going there for a long time besides a great food the one thing that keeps us going it’s a great waitress staff especially Britney who has taken care of us the whole time. We sometimes I have 30 or more people as she takes care of us all a lot of our guys   me how   she do it I don’t know but she does

I have meant to try their rotisserie chicken for a while. I ordered a blacken whole Peruvian chicken with 2 sides, rice and beans and French fries. The chicken was a bit dry compared with the other local rotisserie chicken restaurants. The sauce is very good but they only give you 6 small containers (3 mild and 3 hot sauce) for a whole chicken. Additional sauce costs extra. The sauce definitely will help with the dry chicken breast.  The restaurant has a pleasant and clean appearance and the workers there are very friendly.

I grabbed some lunch to go. I ordered a  quarter dark and a peach lemon aid. They packed my tray up with yucca and rice. Chicken was good. Sauce was awesome. I got this meal with a drink for about $10 bucks. Parking here is hard to find here at certain times but I got lucky.
Friendly service and I enjoyed the food.

Was really happy. Had huge portions of really tasty food at a 'wow that was cheap' price that is hard to find in the beltway. Could basically order a meal and split it between two people, or have two meals and take it home.
Excellent Food and service! Everything was cooked perfectly!

I ordered for delivery late night and food came fast. I ordered Singapore mei fun, and beef and scallops. The noodle was very good and I was able to substitute the pork for beef so that was great. Thank you for that. Although I was annoyed that the garnish/condiments I asked for were spilled when they arrived but at least it was in small packets so it didn’t spill all over.

As for the beef and scallops... :( maybe it was my fault, I usually have a reservation about where I order from to satisfy my craving for seafood, and usually do so from restaurants that actually specialize in seafood. That way I don’t have to blame a restaurant for getting it wrong if that was not their specialty to begin with. In this case however, I figured since I saw good stars for sushi and was in the mood for some scallops, figured I’ll try it. That was a bad idea. The scallops were so rubbery and the beef was so slimy that I just could not take another bite. The beef especially was awful. I mean I can understand rubbery from being overcooked probably from just being reheated but the beef just indicated that maybe the dish was going bad. Additionally, I couldn’t even appreciate the good portion of the dish because it inappropriately came with a small side  of rice to accompanying it.

I'm surprised at the 4 and 5 star reviews. If you look at my profile, I'm an easy man to please with Asian food. This had to be one of my worst experiences out of the several cities I've lived in. Our Singapore Mei Fun was bland (and that's my typical go to for every new Chinese restaurant). Our green beans were mush. Our wanton soup was literally so bad we spit it back out; the wantons were grainy and the soup smelled and tasted foul, like dirty pipe water. Even the fortune cookies were old and stale that we spit it out. The plain white rice was somehow the best part of the meal, and to be fair, the salmon roll and dumplings were decent. Either this was a bad day, or this is not a 5 or 4 star restaurant. Highly disappointed.

We order from here consisently and it's always good. We order more sushi than Chinese food and it's always fresh and delicious. It won't be the best sushi you've ever had but there's very little good  (or any) sushi to choose from in this area and Spring Garden is by far our favorite!
Don't hang up on people after charging their credit card over $100. Food is fine, service is awful.
Honestly one of the best!!!! Great portions very filling! Also very fresh!😄😄😄

Asked for battered chicken party wings and they didn’t batter them so I had plain tasteless chicken. Bland Mac and cheese as well as the potato salad. I spend $55 for no reason. This location is the only one that disappoints.

I will begin by saying the food was delicious, but...the service is not very good.

I spent just over $100 on dinner for my family.  I ordered 2 lamb over rice from the fajita menu that was supposed to come with a white sauce,  but when I got home I discovered there was none in my bags. So the lamb and rice fajita was dry.

I also ordered a 15 piece fried chicken with 3 sides, and only received 2 of those 3 sides. The other items in my order were correct.

The young man at the counter obviously didn't want to be there and slow as molasses. When I called to let them know about what was missing, he had absolutely nothing to say. I only trying to determine how I could get the missing items, but all he had to say was that the manager was not there.

We order out a lot,  but if this is typical of the service here, I don't think I will be ordering from here again.

reviews.author_name: Unique & Interesting People of the World
reviews.text: My daughter and I ordered food here.  The personality of the male cashier was nice.  The restaurant is dead silent.  No music, no tv.  I ordered a whiting sandwich combo.  I took a few bites out of it and had to throw it away.  The fish tastes too fishy.  Like it was fried in cod liver oil.  My daughter got chicken greens and Mac and cheese.  She said the items were good but not enough to want to order from here again.

This is my second visit to this location. The first visit we order fish, they cooked the heart and soul out of the fish.  We had to return the fish and get chicken, the chicken was very good.  Returned a week later and the chicken is horrible it does not taste like lasts weeks chicken at all....NO FLAVOR.    The young man that works the counter is clueless and has no personality and a now caring attitude.  I will not be returning.

Hard pressed to leave bad reviews but will for this location specifically. Haven't had issues at other spots but the Mac and Cheese I got here was rancid. When I took a bite I thought I accidentally got buffalo flavor or something. Nope it was just that rank. I used to love the chicken and waffles but can't go back after this
Delicious food and super friendly
They have some of the best food. They have the best service. I recommend coming here.

Delicious food
And  good customer service, a clean place.
I recommend this place.🌮🌮
The best birria Tacos highly recommend
The best food  truck in the área. Amazing service.. recommend
Great experience! Had the lobster roll and cod sandwich. Live this place - will be back. East parking! Great staff!

This place is not even open. The GM - Alex Berentzen is posting fake reviews for all Willie T locations.
Please report all fake reviews, they are destroying the integrity of the people posting true unbiased reviews.
Thank you!
